          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px;"> What are the obstacles to maintaining the ceasefire?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The recent Israeli-Hamas ceasefire-hostage deal took effect last Sunday. While it was a relief to many, it opened a lot of questions on what was next. The deal took 15 months and didn‚Äôt drastically change from the one proposed a year ago. It‚Äôs very fragile. These are some of the main limitations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Lack of trust:</strong> Both sides will likely accuse each other of <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-01-2025-6-breaking-the-rules" target="_blank">breaking the rules</a>. Nethyanhu delayed the finalization of the deal a couple of days to appease the far right of the parliament. Hamas was slow to give the list of the hostages. Israel has already started striking in the West Bank, claiming it is to counter terrorist attacks.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Political polarization:</strong> This is an issue for both sides. Israeli society remains very polarized (<a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-01-2025-7-political-survey" target="_blank">political survey</a>). Netanyahu is unpopular with a lot of Israeli society. He also had problems among the right wing, which protested his deal, signaling the exit of some of the members of his coalition. In return, the PM of the Palestinian Authority said Hamas shouldn‚Äôt control Gaza.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Trump‚Äôs presidency:</strong> Trump claims credit for part of a ceasefire resolution and insists that the deal be done before he takes office. However, he contributed to the recent strikes in the West Bank by <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-01-2025-8-lifting-the-sanctions" target="_blank">lifting the sanctions</a> on some of the settlers put in place by the Biden Administration. This could be seen as enabling Israel to demand total victory over Palestine.</p>
        </mj-text>
